# Plan structure (mandatory)

Every plan MUST include these sections, concisely:

1. **Problem (user words)** — one short paragraph
2. **Current implementation** — what it does, what problem it was meant to solve, what it does right/wrong (general, not one-off)
3. **Proposed change** — what changes, outcome if kept vs applied, edge cases
4. **Validation** — how to verify across cases; bare-wrapper or log comparison when pipeline vs model is disputed

Rules: correct fix over line-count bias; no arbitrary caps without approval; no strip/hide as primary fix when root cause is injection/routing.
